{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1552,"text":"This man is wearing what we call"},{"time":4266,"text":"a bee beard. (Laughter)"},{"time":7036,"text":"A beard full of bees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8485,"text":"Now, this is what many of you might picture"},{"time":11728,"text":"when you think about honeybees, maybe insects,"},{"time":14701,"text":"or maybe anything that has more legs than two."},{"time":17789,"text":"And let me start by telling you, I gotcha."},{"time":20447,"text":"I understand that. But, there are many things to know,"},{"time":24928,"text":"and I want you to open your minds here,"},{"time":27608,"text":"keep them open, and change your perspective about honeybees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31098,"text":"Notice that this man is not getting stung."},{"time":34063,"text":"He probably has a queen bee tied to his chin,"},{"time":37507,"text":"and the other bees are attracted to it."},{"time":39626,"text":"So this really demonstrates our relationship with honeybees,"},{"time":43662,"text":"and that goes deep back for thousands of years."},{"time":47430,"text":"We're very co-evolved, because we depend on bees"},{"time":50592,"text":"for pollination and, even more recently,"},{"time":53552,"text":"as an economic commodity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55376,"text":"Many of you may have heard that honeybees are disappearing,"},{"time":58176,"text":"not just dying, but they're gone."},{"time":60753,"text":"We don't even find dead bodies."},{"time":62555,"text":"This is called colony collapse disorder,"},{"time":64926,"text":"and it's bizarre. Researchers around the globe"},{"time":67138,"text":"still do not know what's causing it,"},{"time":69584,"text":"but what we do know is that, with the declining numbers"},{"time":72154,"text":"of bees, the costs of over 130 fruit and vegetable crops"},{"time":76391,"text":"that we rely on for food is going up in price."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81398,"text":"So honeybees are important for their role in the economy"},{"time":85156,"text":"as well as in agriculture."},{"time":87181,"text":"Here you can see some pictures of what are called"},{"time":89000,"text":"green roofs, or urban agriculture."},{"time":91689,"text":"We're familiar with the image on the left that shows"},{"time":93967,"text":"a local neighborhood garden in the South End."},{"time":96751,"text":"That's where I call home. I have a beehive in the backyard."},{"time":99542,"text":"And perhaps a green roof in the future,"},{"time":101961,"text":"when we're further utilizing urban areas,"},{"time":103892,"text":"where there are stacks of garden spaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107350,"text":"Check out this image above the orange line in Boston."},{"time":110703,"text":"Try to spot the beehive. It's there."},{"time":114180,"text":"It's on the rooftop, right on the corner there,"},{"time":116877,"text":"and it's been there for a couple of years now."},{"time":119270,"text":"The way that urban beekeeping currently operates"},{"time":122522,"text":"is that the beehives are quite hidden,"},{"time":125113,"text":"and it's not because they need to be."},{"time":127140,"text":"It's just because people are uncomfortable with the idea,"},{"time":130117,"text":"and that's why I want you today to try to think about this,"},{"time":133791,"text":"think about the benefits of bees in cities"},{"time":136074,"text":"and why they really are a terrific thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138333,"text":"Let me give you a brief rundown on how pollination works."},{"time":141303,"text":"So we know flowers, we know fruits and vegetables,"},{"time":143886,"text":"even some alfalfa in hay that the livestock"},{"time":147092,"text":"for the meats that we eat, rely on pollinators,"},{"time":149555,"text":"but you've got male and female parts to a plant here,"},{"time":152988,"text":"and basically pollinators are attracted to plants"},{"time":155878,"text":"for their nectar, and in the process,"},{"time":158905,"text":"a bee will visit some flowers and pick up some pollen,"},{"time":162280,"text":"or that male kind of sperm counterpart, along the way,"},{"time":165712,"text":"and then travel to different flowers, and eventually"},{"time":168330,"text":"an apple, in this case, will be produced."},{"time":171449,"text":"You can see the orientation. The stem is down."},{"time":173716,"text":"The blossom end has fallen off by the time we eat it,"},{"time":176670,"text":"but that's a basic overview of how pollination works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179528,"text":"And let's think about urban living, not today,"},{"time":182400,"text":"and not in the past, but what about in a hundred years?"},{"time":185265,"text":"What's it gonna look like? We have huge grand challenges"},{"time":189203,"text":"these days of habitat loss. We have more and more people,"},{"time":193133,"text":"billions of people, in 100 years, God knows how many people,"},{"time":196494,"text":"and how little space there will be to fit all of them,"},{"time":199858,"text":"so we need to change the way that we see cities, and"},{"time":203280,"text":"looking at this picture on the left of New York City today,"},{"time":206643,"text":"you can see how gray and brown it is."},{"time":208510,"text":"We have tar paper on the rooftops that bounces heat back"},{"time":212041,"text":"into the atmosphere,"},{"time":214077,"text":"contributing to global climate change, no doubt."},{"time":216412,"text":"What about in 100 years, if we have green rooftops"},{"time":218912,"text":"everywhere, and gardening, and we create our own crops"},{"time":222075,"text":"right in the cities? We save on the costs of transportation,"},{"time":225878,"text":"we save on a healthier diet, and we also educate"},{"time":229974,"text":"and create new jobs locally."},{"time":231676,"text":"We need bees for the future of our cities and urban living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236342,"text":"Here's some data that we collected through our company"},{"time":239726,"text":"with Best Bees, where we deliver, install and manage"},{"time":242628,"text":"honeybee hives for anybody who wants them,"},{"time":244871,"text":"in the city, in the countryside, and we introduce honeybees,"},{"time":248388,"text":"and the idea of beekeeping in your own backyard or rooftop"},{"time":251247,"text":"or fire escape, for even that matter,"},{"time":253728,"text":"and seeing how simple it is and how possible it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256502,"text":"There's a counterintuitive trend that we noticed"},{"time":258634,"text":"in these numbers. So let's look at the first metric here,"},{"time":262077,"text":"overwintering survival."},{"time":263477,"text":"Now this has been a huge problem for many years,"},{"time":266302,"text":"basically since the late 1980s, when the varroa mite came"},{"time":270362,"text":"and brought many different viruses, bacteria"},{"time":273738,"text":"and fungal diseases with it."},{"time":275542,"text":"Overwintering success is hard,"},{"time":277291,"text":"and that's when most of the colonies are lost,"},{"time":279584,"text":"and we found that in the cities, bees are surviving"},{"time":282250,"text":"better than they are in the country."},{"time":284598,"text":"A bit counterintuitive, right?"},{"time":286826,"text":"We think, oh, bees, countryside, agriculture,"},{"time":288908,"text":"but that's not what the bees are showing."},{"time":291135,"text":"The bees like it in the city. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293284,"text":"Furthermore, they also produce more honey."},{"time":296431,"text":"The urban honey is delicious."},{"time":299000,"text":"The bees in Boston on the rooftop of the Seaport Hotel,"},{"time":302097,"text":"where we have hundreds of thousands of bees"},{"time":304569,"text":"flying overheard right now"},{"time":306072,"text":"that I'm sure none of you noticed when we walked by,"},{"time":308377,"text":"are going to all of the local community gardens"},{"time":310687,"text":"and making delicious, healthy honey"},{"time":313086,"text":"that just tastes like the flowers in our city."},{"time":316114,"text":"So the yield for urban hives, in terms of honey production,"},{"time":320901,"text":"is higher as well as the overwintering survival,"},{"time":324016,"text":"compared to rural areas."},{"time":325390,"text":"Again, a bit counterintuitive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327392,"text":"And looking back historically at the timeline"},{"time":330713,"text":"of honeybee health, we can go back to the year 950 and see"},{"time":334989,"text":"that there was also a great mortality of bees in Ireland."},{"time":338037,"text":"So the problems of bees today isn't necessarily"},{"time":341188,"text":"something new. It has been happening"},{"time":343813,"text":"since over a thousand years ago,"},{"time":345880,"text":"but what we don't really notice are these problems in cities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349577,"text":"So one thing I want to encourage you to think about"},{"time":351605,"text":"is the idea of what an urban island is."},{"time":354007,"text":"You think in the city maybe the temperature's warmer."},{"time":357403,"text":"Why are bees doing better in the city?"},{"time":358982,"text":"This is a big question now to help us understand"},{"time":361654,"text":"why they should be in the city."},{"time":363975,"text":"Perhaps there's more pollen in the city."},{"time":365997,"text":"With the trains coming in to urban hubs, they can"},{"time":368213,"text":"carry pollen with them, very light pollen,"},{"time":370792,"text":"and it's just a big supermarket in the city."},{"time":373129,"text":"A lot of linden trees live along the railroad tracks."},{"time":376956,"text":"Perhaps there are fewer pesticides in the cities"},{"time":379722,"text":"than there are in [rural] areas."},{"time":381940,"text":"Perhaps there are other things that we're just not thinking about yet,"},{"time":384792,"text":"but that's one idea to think about, urban islands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387399,"text":"And colony collapse disorder is not the only thing"},{"time":391323,"text":"affecting honeybees. Honeybees are dying,"},{"time":394225,"text":"and it's a huge, huge grand challenge of our time."},{"time":397929,"text":"What you can see up here is a map of the world,"},{"time":400401,"text":"and we're tracking the spread of this varroa mite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403473,"text":"Now, the varroa mite is what changed the game"},{"time":406161,"text":"in beekeeping, and you can see, at the top right,"},{"time":409016,"text":"the years are changing, we're coming up to modern times,"},{"time":412279,"text":"and you can see the spread of the varroa mite"},{"time":414609,"text":"from the early 1900s through now."},{"time":417260,"text":"It's 1968, and we're pretty much covering Asia."},{"time":420211,"text":"1971, we saw it spread to Europe and South America,"},{"time":424273,"text":"and then, when we get to the 1980s,"},{"time":428661,"text":"and specifically to 1987, the varroa mite finally came"},{"time":432895,"text":"to North America and to the United States,"},{"time":435277,"text":"and that is when the game changed"},{"time":437733,"text":"for honeybees in the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440414,"text":"Many of us will remember our childhood growing up,"},{"time":442502,"text":"maybe you got stung by a bee, you saw bees on flowers."},{"time":444728,"text":"Think of the kids today. Their childhood's a bit different."},{"time":448666,"text":"They don't experience this."},{"time":450590,"text":"The bees just aren't around anymore."},{"time":453090,"text":"So we need bees and they're disappearing and it's a big problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456530,"text":"What can we do here?"},{"time":458235,"text":"So, what I do is honeybee research."},{"time":460800,"text":"I got my Ph.D. studying honeybee health."},{"time":462893,"text":"I started in 2005 studying honeybees."},{"time":466358,"text":"In 2006, honeybees started disappearing,"},{"time":468700,"text":"so suddenly, like, this little nerd kid"},{"time":471061,"text":"going to school working with bugs — (Laughter) —"},{"time":473678,"text":"became very relevant in the world."},{"time":475771,"text":"And it worked out that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476852,"text":"So my research focuses on ways to make bees healthier."},{"time":480851,"text":"I don't research what's killing the bees, per se."},{"time":483642,"text":"I'm not one of the many researchers around the world"},{"time":485825,"text":"who's looking at the effects of pesticides or diseases"},{"time":488896,"text":"or habitat loss and poor nutrition on bees."},{"time":491448,"text":"We're looking at ways to make bees healthier"},{"time":493441,"text":"through vaccines, through yogurt, like probiotics,"},{"time":497072,"text":"and other types of therapies in ways that can be fed orally to bees,"},{"time":501872,"text":"and this process is so easy, even a 7-year-old can do it."},{"time":504907,"text":"You just mix up some pollen, sugar and water,"},{"time":507267,"text":"and whatever active ingredient you want to put in,"},{"time":509069,"text":"and you just give it right to the bees. No chemicals involved,"},{"time":511267,"text":"just immune boosters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513437,"text":"Humans think about our own health in a prospective way."},{"time":515637,"text":"We exercise, we eat healthy, we take vitamins."},{"time":518297,"text":"Why don't we think about honeybees in that same type of way?"},{"time":521340,"text":"Bring them to areas where they're thriving"},{"time":523906,"text":"and try to make them healthier before they get sick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527342,"text":"I spent many years in grad school trying to poke bees and do vaccines"},{"time":531531,"text":"with needles. (Laughter) Like, years,"},{"time":534873,"text":"years at the bench, \"Oh my gosh, it's 3 a.m."},{"time":537175,"text":"and I'm still pricking bees.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":538526,"text":"And then one day I said, \"Why don't we just do an oral vaccine?\""},{"time":542400,"text":"It's like, \"Ugh,\" so that's what we do. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":547048,"text":"I'd love to share with you some images of urban beehives,"},{"time":550236,"text":"because they can be anything."},{"time":552718,"text":"I mean, really open your mind with this."},{"time":554621,"text":"You can paint a hive to match your home."},{"time":556795,"text":"You can hide a hive inside your home."},{"time":560165,"text":"These are three hives on the rooftop"},{"time":561977,"text":"of the Fairmont Copley Plaza Hotel,"},{"time":564088,"text":"and they're beautiful here. I mean, we matched"},{"time":566548,"text":"the new color of the inside of their rooms to do"},{"time":569229,"text":"some type of a stained wood with blue for their sheets,"},{"time":572466,"text":"and these bees are terrific, and they also will use"},{"time":575485,"text":"herbs that are growing in the garden."},{"time":578091,"text":"That's what the chefs go to to use for their cooking,"},{"time":581190,"text":"and the honey -- they do live events --"},{"time":583069,"text":"they'll use that honey at their bars."},{"time":585207,"text":"Honey is a great nutritional substitute for regular sugar"},{"time":587827,"text":"because there are different types of sugars in there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589954,"text":"We also have a classroom hives project,"},{"time":592331,"text":"where -- this is a nonprofit venture --"},{"time":594983,"text":"we're spreading the word around the world for how"},{"time":598100,"text":"honeybee hives can be taken into the classroom"},{"time":600385,"text":"or into the museum setting, behind glass,"},{"time":602691,"text":"and used as an educational tool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605099,"text":"This hive that you see here has been"},{"time":606723,"text":"in Fenway High School for many years now."},{"time":609274,"text":"The bees fly right into the outfield of Fenway Park."},{"time":611233,"text":"Nobody notices it. If you're not a flower,"},{"time":613188,"text":"these bees do not care about you. (Laughter)"},{"time":615809,"text":"They don't. They don't. They'll say,"},{"time":618180,"text":"\"S'cuse me, flying around.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":621091,"text":"Some other images here in telling a part of the story"},{"time":623654,"text":"that really made urban beekeeping terrific is"},{"time":626292,"text":"in New York City, beekeeping was illegal until 2010."},{"time":629656,"text":"That's a big problem, because what's going to pollinate"},{"time":632993,"text":"all of the gardens and the produce locally? Hands?"},{"time":636417,"text":"I mean, locally in Boston, there is a terrific company"},{"time":639773,"text":"called Green City Growers, and they are going"},{"time":642178,"text":"and pollinating their squash crops by hand with Q-Tips,"},{"time":645689,"text":"and if they miss that three day window, there's no fruit."},{"time":648243,"text":"Their clients aren't happy, and people go hungry."},{"time":651146,"text":"So this is important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653014,"text":"We have also some images of honey from Brooklyn."},{"time":655121,"text":"Now, this was a mystery in the New York Times"},{"time":657073,"text":"where the honey was very red, and the"},{"time":658921,"text":"New York State forensics department came in"},{"time":660445,"text":"and they actually did some science to match"},{"time":663047,"text":"the red dye with that found"},{"time":665567,"text":"in a maraschino cherry factory down the street. (Laughter)"},{"time":668818,"text":"So you can tailor your honey to taste however you want"},{"time":672216,"text":"by planting bee-friendly flowers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674511,"text":"Paris has been a terrific model for urban beekeeping."},{"time":677249,"text":"They've had hives on the rooftop of their opera house"},{"time":679799,"text":"for many years now, and that's what really got people started, thinking,"},{"time":682735,"text":"\"Wow, we can do this, and we should do this.\""},{"time":686203,"text":"Also in London, and in Europe across the board,"},{"time":689036,"text":"they're very advanced in their use of green rooftops"},{"time":692288,"text":"and integrating beehives,"},{"time":694786,"text":"and I'll show you an ending note here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697967,"text":"I would like to encourage you to open your mind."},{"time":700042,"text":"What can you do to save the bees or to help them"},{"time":703203,"text":"or to think of sustainable cities in the future?"},{"time":706994,"text":"Well, really, just change your perspective."},{"time":708964,"text":"Try to understand that bees are very important."},{"time":710938,"text":"A bee isn't going to sting you if you see it."},{"time":713349,"text":"The bee dies. Honeybees die when they sting,"},{"time":716663,"text":"so they don't want to do it either. (Laughter)"},{"time":719105,"text":"It's nothing to panic about. They're all over the city."},{"time":723195,"text":"You could even get your own hive if you want."},{"time":725297,"text":"There are great resources available,"},{"time":727025,"text":"and there are even companies that will help get you set up and mentor you"},{"time":729981,"text":"and it's important for our educational system in the world"},{"time":733107,"text":"for students to learn about agriculture worldwide"},{"time":735793,"text":"such as this little girl, who, again, is not even getting stung."},{"time":739628,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}